# Error Documentation

# Common Error Messages

---

## Error 400 — Bad Request

### Description

The server could not process your request because the information sent was invalid or incomplete.

### Possible Causes

- Required fields are missing.
- Incorrect data format.
- Invalid request parameters.

### Resolution

- Check that all required fields are completed.
- Verify the information entered.
- Refresh the page and try again.

---

## Error 401 — Unauthorized

### Description

Authentication is required before accessing this resource.

### Possible Causes

- You are not logged in.
- Your session has expired.
- Invalid login credentials.

### Resolution

- Sign in again.
- Verify your email and password.
- Reset your password if necessary.

---

## Error 403 — Forbidden

### Description

You are authenticated but do not have permission to perform this action.

### Possible Causes

- Your account lacks the required permissions.
- Administrator-only feature.
- Access restrictions.

### Resolution

- Contact your administrator.
- Verify your account permissions.
- Request access if appropriate.

---

## Error 404 — Not Found

### Description

The requested page or resource could not be found.

### Possible Causes

- Incorrect URL.
- Deleted resource.
- Broken link.

### Resolution

- Check the web address.
- Return to the homepage.
- Search for the content again.

---

## Error 500 — Internal Server Error

### Description

An unexpected error occurred on the server.

### Possible Causes

- Temporary server issue.
- Software bug.
- Unexpected system failure.

### Resolution

- Refresh the page after a few minutes.
- Try again later.
- Contact support if the problem persists.

---

# Troubleshooting Tips

Before contacting support:

- Refresh the page.
- Clear your browser cache.
- Try another browser.
- Check your internet connection.
- Sign out and sign back in.

